    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-07-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-07-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="170"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Prime Minister <persName type="from">Churchill</persName> to
                        President <persName type="to">Roosevelt</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d170fn1">Channel of transmission not indicated.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">most secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-07-19">19 July
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>371. <gloss target="#t_FNP1">Former Naval Person</gloss> to President Roosevelt
                    personal and most secret. Most immediate.</p>
                <p>Should be most grateful to know at earliest moment whether your <gloss
                        target="#t_UJ1">UJ</gloss> plan is on. Meanwhile I am setting everything in
                    train that can be done most secretly for our rendezvous on 15th. The development
                    of post “<gloss target="#t_Husky1">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Husky</hi>
                    </gloss>” seems to render this all the more urgent. Moreover I am most anxious
                    to learn from you how we are to finish up Japan and <pb facs="0508" n="394"
                        xml:id="pg_394"/> what is the best plan. You will readily understand that
                    enormous preparations, moral, political and material, have to be made in this
                    country in order that our power may be fully transferred to the Far East when
                    the time comes. We cannot too early begin these studies. We will finish [<hi
                        rend="italic">furnish</hi>] your staffs with a synopsis of points for
                    discussion before we set out.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
